WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:20.000
Narrator: The Christmas Sing is a cherished tradition in the village, held every year on Christmas Eve.

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:45.000
Narrator: The town hall is decorated with holly and evergreen as families gather after a shared supper.

00:00:45.000 --> 00:01:10.000
Narrator: Voices rise in harmony as singers perform psalms and festive songs, filling the hall with warmth.

00:01:10.000 --> 00:01:40.000
Narrator: Among the crowd, old tensions and quiet rivalries fade into the background of music.

00:01:40.000 --> 00:02:10.000
Narrator: The conductor raises his baton, guiding the singers through waves of sound and emotion.

00:02:10.000 --> 00:02:40.000
Narrator: By the end of the night, new connections are formed, and long-standing misunderstandings begin to heal.

00:02:40.000 --> 00:03:10.000
Narrator: As the singers return home under the winter sky, the village feels changed—closer, warmer, and more united.
